        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 16 at 12:58PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1258 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Magdalena, or 14 miles northwest of Socorro, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mainly rural areas of Central Socorro County.

This includes Highway 60 between Mile Markers 117 and 124.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.</instruction>
